post_content:

357 MAGNUM KIT

Everything you need is included in this kit except engine and clutch.

Add a Clutch in Product Options,  Then scroll down to add an Engine.

Back in the 60’s, it was every boys dream to have a minibike. We could not wait to get home from school and go down to the field and ride.

The 357 minibike is designed after the Taco 22 as sold by Steen’s back in the days of Taco, Bonanza, Rupp and a host of others.

WARNING DEATH OR INJURY
can result from improper maintenance or use of this product. for use on Close Course Competition only and is NOT street legal. Must be 16 years of age with proper Adult Supervision. See additional safety and warning information, click on Minibike Warning below and INFO above

BUILDER NOTES:
A stock engine may not fit on this frame unless you remove the Gas Tank. Most stock 4-7hp engines including Honda GX120/160/200, Titan TX200 with side-fill tank, Predator 212 and others can be installed by removing the stock Gas Tank, Air Filter and Exhaust and installing an external Gas Tank and our Mikuni Stage 1 kit with Fatty or Stinger Exhaust Header

Custom Bike Pictured with the Stage 1 kit, not included. Use the Mikuni stage 1 kit with Fatty or Stinger to install a 22mm Mikuni Carburetor on your Honda GX120, GX160, GX200 or clone including Predator and Titan engine. Kit includes: Intake Manifold, 22mm Genuine Mikuni Carb, High Flow Air Filter and Fatty Exhaust Header Pipe.

post_title: Brake Drum with 6″ or 7″ Tires and 8mm Studs – Version 13822
post_content:
Description

Chinese ATV Front Wheel Hub – Taotao ATA110B with 6″ or 7″ Tires and Front Drum Brakes

This front wheel hub is used on several makes and models of Chinese kid’s ATVs. The best way to insure you are ordering the correct part is to use our detail pictures and measurements.  Please be sure to check both before ordering.

Hub details:

  • Used with 6″ and 7″ tires
  • Overall width of cylinder: 95mm [3.7″]
  • ID of drum: 85mm
  • (3) M8 x 1.25 studs
  • Stud distance apart: 77mm [3.04″] center-to-center
  • Center hole diameter: 18mm [.71″]
  • Bearing size: BB6003RS
  • Seal size: 22x35x5
  • For front DRUM brakes
  • 108878  13822A2136

We have two brake drums which are very similar.  The difference between them is the size of the studs and how far apart they are, so please measure yours before ordering.

Hub is known to fit the Taotao  ATA110B, ATA110B1 and the ATA110 Boulder. Be sure to check your hub measurements with the above measurements to be sure you are getting the correct part.

post_title: Chinese 12v Battery Charger with Detachable Wire
post_content:
Description

Chinese 12v Battery Charger with Detachable Wire

12 volt battery charger with detachable wire for permanent mounting to ATV, dirt bike, etc.  Fasten the wire to the battery and the battery charger screws onto the other end of the wire.  Allows you to charge the battery without getting all the way to it every time.

Charger specs:

  • Part that attaches to unit has 1/4″ eyelets with an 8″ lead.
  • Protective rubber cover to keep out elements.
  • Battery charger plugs directly into outlet
  • Charger has a 20 inch lead wire.
  • 3 prong connection.

post_content:
Description

Gas Powered Drift Trike with 6.5hp engine

Ever wondered what it would be like riding a big wheel with a huge shot of nitrous? This new drift trike is just that and it is seriously fun. Heavy duty tubular steel frame with a 6.5 horsepower engine connected to metal banded rear go kart tires for maximum drifting action. Wide bmx style handlebars with rubber grips let you control the wide street tread tire mounted on the 16” front wheel equipped with hand operated disc brakes.

– Tubular steel frame
– Front disc brakes with hand lever
– Threadless headset
– BMX style handlebar and stem
– Soft rubber handgrips
– Adjustable foot pegs
– Hard molded racing seat
– 26” Front wheel with wide street tire
– Plastic sleeved rear wheels for maximum drift ability
– 6.5 Horsepower gasoline engine

 

AKA motorized Big wheel, 3 wheeler, Drift Kart

Description

Exhaust Muffler System Assembly for Coleman 196cc Mini Bikes and Go-Karts

This exhaust is the oem muffler for the Coleman BT200X, CT200U and CT200U-EX mini bike.  Also used on the KT196 Coleman go-kart.

Exhaust details:

  • Compatible with 196cc 4 stroke, GX200 168F Honda clone engines
  • Muffler with heat shield
  • Basic dimensions: 5.3″ x 4.75″ x 5.8″ includes manifold pipe but not exhaust guard
  • Manifold pipe holes are 44mm {1.7″] center-to-center
  • Includes exhaust guard over output hole
  • 18000/168F

This muffler probably fits other 168F engine applications.  Please check pictures and measurements before ordering.

post_title: Exhaust System / Muffler for Taotao ATA110B ATV – Version 14
post_content:
Description

Taotao ATA110B ATV Exhaust System

Version 14

This exhaust is known to fit the TaoTao ATA110B.  Please verify the measurements before purchasing this exhaust.  May fit other makes and models.

Exhaust details:

  • Overall length: 28″
  • Silencer length: 9″
  • Silencer OD: 3″
  • Pipe OD: 1″
  • Pipe end OD: 1.25″
  • Pipe ID: .75″
  • Pipe end ID: 1″
  • Mounting “eye” bracket for head: 1.85″ center to center on mounting holes
  • Pipe comes out at an angle on bottom of silencer
  • 1st bend is 9″ from silencer
  • 2nd bend is 9″ from 1st bend and goes towards center of ATV.
  • 3rd bend is 3″ from 2nd bend and curves upward to mount into cylinder head.
  • 20638B438  101752

We don’t get any exhaust assemblies that are cosmetically perfect.  They all have a few “dings” and “scratches” on them from their overseas journey.  If you need a perfect one, better to buy somewhere else.

Known to fit TaoTao ATA110B, ATA110B1, ATA110B3, Eagle 110B1, FA70, FA90, BY110, FA110, Boulder 110 and more.

Description

FALCON 200 MINIBIKE 
Some assembly required

6.5hp Pull Start Engine, Automatic Torque Converter, Front Suspension, Adult size Large Frame, Large Tires, Headlight, Fenders. some assembly required

The affordably priced Falcon 200 will go over most trails where a standard minibike can’t go! The 6.5hp engine can take on trail riding with its large ATV wheels and tires give it plenty of ground clearance for rugged terrain. The padded seat is mounted on springs for a softer ride. The larger frame allows a larger rider to operate the bike more easily than a smaller minibike. Other features include wide steel fenders and an engine shut off switch.

The Falcon 200 is designed for off-road use and are capable of traveling on grass, sand, gravel, mud, and firm snow. They have have a very low center of gravity for ease of maneuverability. The Falcon 200 offers plenty of fun and power while being inexpensive to maintain and operate. Falcon trail bikes are a great all around sport utility bike to use on your hunting, fishing, and camping trips. The Falcon 200 can provide year-round recreation for the adult rider.

Specs

  • Engine: single cylinder, 4-Stroke, 200cc Engine
  • cooling: air cooling
  • Ignition: C.D.I
  • Compression Ratio: 8.8:1
  • Bore and Stroke:　39×41.4
  • Max Power: 6.5 hp
  • Starting: Recoil
  • Gas Tank Capacity: 3.6 L

  • Dry Weight: 132lbs.
  • Seat Height: 22.8″

  • Ground Clearance: 5″
  • Weight Capacity: 190lbs.

post_content:
Description

FRIJOLE® MINIBIKE FRAME

Build a Frijole Mini Bike. For experienced builders only!

*FRAME ONLY – The Wheels, Tires, Engine, Stinger Exhaust, Cylindrical Gas Tank, and optional Mikuni Carb kit shown in the photos are NOT INCLUDED with this kit, but are sold separately.

Back in the 60’s, it was every boys dream to have a minibike. We could not wait to get home from school and go down to the field and ride.

This is the genuine Frijole Minibike as sold by Steens back in the days of Taco, Bonanza, Rupp and a host of others.

WARNING Death or Injury may occur. Mini Bike Warning

FRAME KIT INCLUDED

  • FRAME
  • FORK and BOLT
  • MONSTER GREEN
  • DECALS

Download the ASSEMBLY GUIDE

OTHER PARTS THAT CAN BE USED:

  • 6.5hp Engine, 196cc (Not Included)
  • Centrifugal Clutch (Not Included)
  • 6″ Wheels, Split-Rim Polished Aluminum
  • 1″ Heavy Duty Frame with 7/8″ Handlebars
  • #35 Chain with 72T Sprocket
  • 4-1/2″ Rear Drum Brake
  • Tires: F / R: Sawtooth/Knobby
  • Bike Weight: 65 lbs
  • Max Speed: 37mph (stock engine)
  • Max load: 190 lbs
  • Wheelbase: 32
  • Seat Height: 24″
  • Ground Clearance: 5″

WARNING DEATH OR INJURY can result from improper maintenance or use of this product. for use on Close Course Competition only and is NOT street legal. Must be 16 years of age with proper Adult Supervision. This kit does NOT include a Chain Guard, You must install a Chain Guard when you install an engine on this kit. Do not operate without a chain guard. See additional safety and warning information, click on Minibike Warning above

BUILDER NOTES:

You will have to relocate or remove the stock gas tank and exhaust to install a 6.5hp Honda, Titan or clone motor on the Frijole Minibike.

A stock engine may not fit on this frame unless you remove the Gas Tank. Most stock 4-7hp engines including Honda GX120/160/200, Titan TX200 with side-fill tank, Predator 212 and others can be installed by removing the stock Gas Tank, Air Filter and Exhaust and installing an external Gas Tank and our Mikuni Stage 1 kit with Stinger Exhaust Header. The Fatty exhaust does not fit the Frijole Frame.

Custom Bike Pictured with the Stage 1 kit, not included. Use the Mikuni stage 1 kit with Stinger to install a 22mm Mikuni Carburetor on your Honda GX120, GX160, GX200 or clone including Predator and Titan engine. Kit includes: Intake Manifold, 22mm  Mikuni Carb, High Flow Air Filter and Stinger Exhaust Header Pipe.

post_title: Front Wheel Hub – Hammerhead, ASW, Carter Go-Kart
post_content:
Description

Chinese Go-Kart Front Wheel Hub

Version 85

This front wheel hub was used on several makes and models of Chinese go-karts including American Sportworks, Carter and Hammerhead. The best way to insure you are ordering the correct part is to use our detail pictures and measurements.  Please be sure to check both before ordering.

Hub details:

  • Black
  • Width: 68.4mm [2.69″]
  • (4) 10mm*1.25 studs included and installed
  • Studs are 78mm [3.07″] apart center-to-center, side to side
  • Studs are 110mm [4.33″] apart center-to-center across
  • 6202 & 6204 included and installed
  • The 6202 bearing is on the side with the studs
  • The OD of the 6202 is 35mm [1.38] ID is 15mm [.59″]
  • The 6204 bearing is on the side with the six bolt holes
  • The OD of the 6204 is 47mm [1.85″] ID is 20mm [.78″]
  • 25*47*7 seal
  • (6) 6mm*1.00 threaded bolt holes
  • Threaded holes are 29mm [1.14″] center-to-center
  • Used with front wheels with 4/110 bolt pattern
  • Does not come with wheel nuts
  • 8.010.085  520-3006  14148

post_content:
Description

The 49cc Gas Pocket Bike is the ultimate kid or adult ride! Great for driveway and parking lot fun, cruise around cones and speed through trails with ease. Comes standard with front & rear disc brakes and large 11 inch pneumatic street tires.

SAFETY FIRST – ALWAYS WEAR YOUR HELMET AND ALL SAFETY EQUIPMENT and observe safe riding rules!!!

Specs:Motor: 49cc 2-Stroke, Air Cooled, EPA Approved
Engine Start: Pull Start
Gas Tank: 1.2 liters
Cruising Range: 20 miles per tank
Fuel/Oil: Unleaded / 2-stroke Oil 32:1
Transmission: Centrifugal (chain drive)
Pocket Bike Size: L=39in, W=20in, H=23in

Seat Height: 18in
Recommended Age: 13+
Max Rider Weight: 170 lbs
Frame: Rigid Steel
Tires: 90/65-6.5 Pneumatic (11 inch)
Brakes: 1 disc front, 1 disc rear
Throttle: Variable twist-grip
Seat: Padded (single rider)
Handlebars: Angle Adjustable, Not Height
Assembly Required: Yes
Box Size: 40x14x26 inches
Box Weight: 57 lbs
Product decoration and specifications subject to change without notice.
Warranty: 30 days parts replacement

post_content:
Description

This motor was developed by Honda to provide a low cost, reliable engine package for beginning kid karters to utilize.
The Honda GX50 engine is factory sealed and will provide young competitors with a super reliable package with no special tuning allowed other than carburetor jetting.

The Kid Kart class is typically ran between the ages of 5 to 8.

Specifications:

  •  Engine Type: Production based 4-cycle single cylinder
  • Displacement: 49cc (2.99 cubic inches)
  • Valvetrain: Single camshaft, push rod two valves per cylinder
  • Crankshaft: Steel alloy two main bearings
  • Pistons: Forged aluminum alloy
  • Connecting Rods: Forged alloy steel
  • Ignition System: Transistorized magneto
  • Lubrication: Splash
  • Cooling: Air Cooled
  • Transmission: N/A
  • Fuel: 91 octane unleaded
  • Weight: 12.1 lbs (5.5 kg)

Description

The Mini Swift is IAME’s entry engine into Karting for ages 9 to 13. This package is simple to start, operate and maintain for new or experienced racers. Delivered as a spec engine package complete with centrifugal clutch, carburetor, air box, exhaust system, electric starter, battery, electrical harness and all necessary mounting hardware.

  • Application: TaG Cadet
  • Engine Type: Kart
  • Bore: Ø 41.80 mm
  • Max Bore: Ø 42.07 mm
  • Stroke: 43.15 mm max
  • Carb. Model: Tillotson HW-31A (Venturi 17mm)
  • Inlet System: piston valve
  • Transmission: dry centrifugal clutch
  • Cooling System: air cooled
  • Starting: electric

post_content:
Description

The X30 has been designed with the specific aim to provide Karting drivers with an innovative yet faithful to tradition engine. The IAME X30 offers modern features, such as the electric starter, the balancer shaft and the water cooling, yet preserving traditional Karting engines aspects, such as the diaphragm carburettor and no power valve. The result is an engine that offers a pure Karting driving experience, combined with ease of use and low maintenance.

Available in standard or junior restricted configuration.
Technical Specifications

Engine Type: single cylinder 2 stroke
Bore: Ø 54.00 mm
Max Bore: Ø 54.28 mm
Stroke: 54.00 mm
Displacement: 123.67cc (125cc max)
Carb. Model: Tillotson HW-27A
Inlet System: reed valve
Lubrication: oil mixture 4%
Ignition System: digital with battery charger
Transmission: dry centrifugal clutch
Cooling System: water cooled
Starting: on-board electric starter
Max Power: 28 Hp (21 Hp ) at 11.750 Rpm
Max Torque: 17 Nm (13Nm) at 10.750 Rpm
Max RPM Limit: 16.000 Rpm (Rpm limiter)

Engine Package Includes

Selettra digital K ignition with pick-up in the stator and generator for battery charging
H.T. coil and vibration dampers
NGK BR9EG sparkplug and resistive spark plug cap
Centrifugal dry clutch group with Z11 detachable sprocket
Tillotson HW-27A Carburetor
Intake silencer with foam air fi lter
Flexible hose with silicon sheath and springs
Exhaust silencer and exhaust header mod. X30
Starter motor external support
X30 electronic box C model – 16.000 RPM
Cables harness with connectors
SSR starter relay
Starter key assembly
Battery support
Velcro strap and dampening rubber pads
Water pump assembly, water pump support, water pump transmission pulley
Water radiator with support
Water hoses and clamps
Thermostat 50°

post_title: Little BadAss 357 Mini Bike CUSTOM Kit
post_content:
Description

357 CUSTOM KIT

Everything you need is included except Engine and Clutch.

Add Engine, Clutch and Performance Parts in Product Options above.

The Stage 1 Kit comes with your choice of Curved (back) or Inverted (Forward) Intake and Mikuni Carb and can be ordered with the Stinger or Fatty Exhaust. It adds about 6hp.

The Cylindrical Gas Tank mounts to the engine and can be ordered in a beautiful powdercoat finish.

The 357 minibike is designed after the Taco 22 as sold by Steen’s back in the days of Taco, Bonanza, Rupp and a host of others.

WARNING Death or Injury may occur. Mini Bike Warning

INCLUDED WITH THIS KIT

  • FRAME
  • FORK and BOLT
  • WHEELS
  • TIRES
  • INNER TUBES
  • SEAT
  • BRAKE
  • SPROCKET
  • CHAIN
  • THROTTLE CONTROLS
  • AXLES
  • KICKSTAND
  • HARDWARE

Supports Titan, Honda, Predator 6.5hp Engine | Comes with 5″ Wheels | High Quality | All Parts Available | MADE-IN-USA

Download the ASSEMBLY GUIDE

Download the INSTRUCTION MANUAL

SPECIFICATIONS:

  • 6.5hp Engine, 196cc (Not Included)
  • Centrifugal Clutch (Not Included)
  • 5″ Wheels, Polished Aluminum
  • 1″ Heavy Duty Frame
  • #35 Chain with 60T Sprocket
  • Foot Scrub Brake
  • Tires: F / R: Knobby
  • Aluminum Kickstand

 

WARNING DEATH OR INJURY can result from improper maintenance or use of this product. for use on Close Course Competition only and is NOT street legal. Must be 16 years of age with proper Adult Supervision. See additional safety and warning information, click on Minibike Warning below and INFO above

BUILDER NOTES: A stock engine may not fit on this frame unless you remove the Gas Tank. Most stock 4-7hp engines including Honda GX120/160/200, Titan TX200 with side-fill tank, Predator 212 and others can be installed by removing the stock Gas Tank, Air Filter and Exhaust and installing an external Gas Tank and our Mikuni Stage 1 kit with Fatty Exhaust Header

Custom Bike Pictured with the Stage 1 kit, not included. Use the Mikuni stage 1 kit with Stinger or Fatty to install a 22mm Mikuni Carburetor on your Honda GX120, GX160, GX200 or clone including Predator and Titan engine. Kit includes: Intake Manifold, 22mm Genuine Mikuni Carb, High Flow Air Filter and Stinger or Fatty Exhaust Header Pipe.

NO WARRANTY All Sales Final. No warranty on kits. Kits are not returnable for any reason and no refunds will be issued. Customer is responsible for painting and assembly of kit. For safety reasons as well as proper operation, we strongly recommend that kits are assembled and/or inspected by a qualified mechanic or persons with appropriate mechanical expertise prior to operation. We cannot refund or exchange your kit if you cannot perform these functions or refuse to let a shop do it for you

post_title: Mikuni Stage 1 Kit, with Fatty Exhaust, for Mini Bike, Go Kart, GX200, Titan, Predator
post_content:
Description

STAGE 1 KIT
adds about 5hp.

INSTALL a 22mm Mikuni Carburetor on your Minibike or Gokart with a Titan TX200, PREDATOR 212, Honda GX120, GX160, GX200 and clones. Curved Intake Manifold brings the carb and intake to optimum position for a minibike. Wake up the power in your engine with this highly recommended kit.

Adding a Mikuni will allow you to adjust fuel mixture and idle speed on-the-fly. You will be able to remove all of the cumbersome stock throttle linkage – including the governor, and slide your throttle cable directly into the carb. You can order our Throttle Linkage kit which includes the cable crimps needed to use your existing cable, or order our replacement cable with the stop already installed

With it’s rugged steel frame and no-dent fenders, this mini bike is built tough to handle the roughest of terrain.

Your Next Adventure is Just a Kick Away

Protect Yourself, Safeguard Your Ride

A Smart Battery Management System (Smart-BMS) constantly monitors your battery’s power levels, keeping you safe and informed, wherever you go.

Description

The perfect KickScooter for your commute.

Combining a sleek design with premium technology, the ES4 electric scooter is a ride you’ll love.

The Next Level of E-Scooter

Are you ready to travel farther and reach your destination with impressive speed? Equipped with internal and external lithium-ion batteries, the Ninebot KickScooter by Segway ES4 has a top speed of nearly 19 MPH and a range of up to 28 miles.

Overheat Protection

Short-Circuit Protection

Overcurrent Protection

Over-Charge Protection

Nominal Power 330W

Peak Power 800W

374 Wh

KickScooter ES4 Features

  • Award-Winning Design

    Winner of the prestigious iF Design Award 2018.

Winner of the prestigious iF Design Award 2018.

  • Built for Performance and Comfort

    The Ninebot KickScooter ES4 has built-in front and rear shock absorbers for a smooth ride, even at high speeds, along with electrical and mechanical brakes for increased safety.

The Ninebot KickScooter ES4 has built-in front and rear shock absorbers for a smooth ride, even at high speeds, along with electrical and mechanical brakes for increased safety.

  • Superior Technology

    The built-in LED display shows your speed and battery life, so you can keep the information you need right in front of you at all times. Turn on the headlight with a quick click of the power button and customize the colors of your rear and side lights to suit your style while providing increased visibility during low-light conditions.

post_content:
Description

The Phantom 49cc Gas Powered Pocket Bike! Standing in at 23 inches in overall height, this tiny monster packs a punch with a 2-stroke 49cc engine. Originally made for adults to race crunched up on tiny motorcycles, pocket bikes have now become popular with kids because of their small size. And you won’t find a wimpy 4-stroke engine on this model, this 2-stroke engine delivers almost twice the power.

Specs:

Motor: 49cc 2-Stroke, Air Cooled, EPA Approved
Engine Start: Pull Start
Gas Tank: 1.25 liters
Cruising Range: 20 miles per tank
Fuel/Oil: Unleaded / 2-stroke Oil 32:1
Transmission: Centrifugal (chain drive)
Pocket Bike Size: L=40in, W=21in, H=23in
Seat Height: 18.5in
Recommended Age: 13+
Max Rider Weight: 170 lbs
Frame: Ridgid Steel
Front Tire: 90/65-6.5 Pneumatic (11 inch)
Rear Tire: 110/50-6.5 Pneumatic (11 inch)
Disk Brakes: Front & Rear
Throttle: Variable twist-grip
Seat: Padded (single rider)
Handlebars: Angle Adjustable, Not Height
Assembly Required: Yes
Box Size: 43x15x26 inches
Box Weight: 56 lbs

Description

The ROK VLR is the perfect engine for the entry-level driver, the ROK VLR not only offers superior performance over its rivals with lower maintenance, but it also offers some great features like electric start. All at a cost racers can afford.

  • Max Power: 20 HP at 9.800 RPM
  • Max Torque: 1,4 KGM at 9.600 RPM
  • Single-cylinder 2 stroke engine
  • Displacement 100 cc
  • Reed Valve
  • Air-cooled system
  • Integrated electrical starter
  • Centrifugal dry-clutch
  • Mixture-lubricated
  • Cast iron made cylinder CNC worked
  • 1 elliptical port plus 2 boosters
  • Piston ring L type
  • Bore and stroke 48x54mm
  • Selettra analogic ignition
  • Butterfly valve 24mm carburetor
  • Vortex intake silencer
  • Engine weight 45 lbs.
  • Engine Weight: 45lbsOPENING ANGLES (all mesurement done with 0.20mm feeler gauge)
    Tolerances: Inlet 126° ± 2°, Exhaust 164° ± 2°
  • Carburetor Butterfly valve/24 mm
  • Generator for battery
  • Charging: On board
  • Electric starter: On board
  • Exhaust with flex: Exhaust with silencer
  • Cylinder AL – SI ALLOY
  • Connecting rod NI – CR – MO STEEL
  • Crankshaft NI – CR – MO STEEL
  • Head AL – SI ALLOY
  • Liner IRON
  • Crankcase AL – SI ALLOY
  • Piston AL – SI ALLOY
  • Piston Ring STEEL OR IRON

post_content:
Description

The revolutionary 125 Max DD2 EVO engine features a 2-speed paddle shift gearbox and a chainless drive system. Steel gear ratios are submerged in oil to create a wet clutch, and replace the traditional chain and sprocket setup. DD2 specific chassis are manufactured with front brakes and a new unique Rear Tyre Protection system to improve safety. The DD2 EVO features an electronic Power Valve. This new system replaces the original adjustable Power Valve and now specifically opens at 8,800rpm or 9,100rpm based on driver preference. The engine requires no additional blueprinting or engine tuning prior to use. The standard setup for the carburettor covers nearly all operating conditions. For extreme conditions the jetting of the carburettor can be changed in between sessions, and no longer requires the driver to ‘tune’ whilst racing. The engine has an integrated electric starter with ignition switch. A 6 month manufacturers warranty is included with the engine.

Complete Airbox, Dellorto VHSB 34 ‘XS’ Carburettor, Fuel Pump, Fuel Filter, Exhaust System, Radiator, Battery, Battery Cradle, Battery Charger, Ignition Coil, Cable Harness, ON/OFF/START Switch, Shift Paddle setup for Steering Wheel.

The ultimate Rotax kart engine that offers more acceleration, faster top speeds and incredible braking power without compromising the high durability, low maintenance and user friendly characteristics of the engine.

post_content:
Description

Out of the box the Rotax 125 Micro Max EVO engine requires no additional blueprinting or engine tuning prior to use. The standard setup of the carburettor covers nearly all operating conditions. For extreme conditions the jetting of the carburettor can be changed in between sessions, and no longer requires the driver to ‘tune’ whilst racing. The engine has an integrated electric starter with ignition switch. It can be upgraded to the Mini, Junior and Senior MAX configurations with just a few components (available as a kit), and includes a 6 month manufacturer’s warranty.

 

Complete Airbox, Dellorto VHSB 34 ‘XS’ Carburettor, Fuel Pump, Fuel Filter, Exhaust System, Radiator, Battery, Battery Cradle, Battery Charger, Ignition Coil, Cable Harness, ON/OFF/START Switch.

 

*battery is no longer included with engine

The Micro MAX engine forgives driving mistakes and is therefore perfect for children to gain their first karting experiences.

post_content:
Description

Out of the box the Rotax 125 Junior Max EVO engine requires no additional blueprinting or engine tuning prior to use. The standard setup of the carburettor covers nearly all operating conditions. For extreme conditions the jetting of the carburettor can be changed in between sessions, and no longer requires the driver to ‘tune’ whilst racing. The engine has an integrated electric starter with ignition switch. It can also be upgraded to the Senior version with just a few components (available as a kit). A 6 month manufacturers warranty is included with the engine.

 

Complete Airbox, Dellorto VHSB 34 ‘XS’ Carburettor, Fuel Pump, Fuel Filter, Exhaust System, Radiator, Battery, Battery Cradle, Battery Charger, Ignition Coil, Cable Harness, ON/OFF/START Switch.

 

*battery is no longer included with engine

A highly durable, low maintenance, user friendly engine perfect for young drivers looking to compete in a high performance junior category.

post_title: ROTAX FR125 SENIOR MAX ENGINE – EVO
post_content:
Description

The Rotax 125 Senior Max EVO engine features an electronic Power Valve. This new system replaces the original adjustable Power Valve and now specifically opens at 7,600rpm or 7,900rpm based on driver preference. The Power Valve creates two port timings to deliver maximum power at low speed and top speed; so you get the best of both worlds. Like the Junior engine, the Senior Max requires no additional blueprinting or engine tuning prior to use. The standard setup of the carburetor covers nearly all operating conditions. For extreme conditions the jetting of the carburetor can be changed in between sessions, and no longer requires the driver to ‘tune’ whilst racing. The engine has an integrated electric starter with ignition switch. It can be downgraded to the Junior version with just a few components (available as a kit). A 6 month manufacturers warranty is included with the engine.

Complete Airbox, Dellorto VHSB 34 ‘XS’ Carburetor, Fuel Pump, Fuel Filter, Exhaust System, Radiator, Battery Cradle, Battery Charger, Ignition Coil, Cable Harness, ON/OFF/START Switch.

A highly durable, low maintenance, user friendly engine perfect for beginners, leisure karters or racers with experience looking to compete in a high performance category.

Description

Smart Self-Balancing Electric Transporter, Intelligent Following Robot.

Features:

  • 11″ Air Filled Tires
  • Smart Safe Lighting System
  • 12.5 mph Top Speed
  • 22 Mile Range
  • 15% Hill Grade
  • Free Mobile App
  • IP54 Splash Proof
  • Physical Controller
  • Smart Battery Management System (BMS)
  • One Button Calling

Qualifies for Free Shipping

The Segway S-PLUS’ powerful motor allows it to quickly accelerate and tackle inclines smoothly.

The 329Wh Li-ion battery, with 1500W output energy, provides the Segway S-PLUS a maximum range of 22 miles.

Keep your valuables safe, and travel worry-free.

You can use the joystick on the included remote control for riderless operation of the S-PLUS.

Turn on Follow Mode via the included remote, and have your Segway S-PLUS follow you.

post_content:
Description

Speedometer Instrument Cluster / Dash Panel Assy for Tao Tao Go-Karts

This is a dash board / dash panel for many go-karts.  What you are buying is a blank panel.  The switches in the pictures are for illustrative purposes only.  Please check pictures and description before ordering.

Dash board details:

  • Black plastic
  • Width: 14.5″
  • Front mounting holes: 298mm [11.73″] apart center-to-center
  • Rear mounting holes: 100mm [3.94″] apart center-to-center
  • (2) 2.22″ openings and (1) .96″ opening
  • 10992A562  102485

Fits Taotao ATK125A, ATK150D, ATK4150 GK110, Targa 150, Targa 200 and Tonga 150.  Also fits the Coleman BK200 go-kart.

Description

  • Smallest kart clutch available on the market today offers the lowest moment of inertia possible
  • Fully adjustable stall speed between 7,800-8,800 or 6,400-7,200 RPM, depending on spring/weight combination
  • Patented TD Technology ensures friction surfaces are isolated to friction discs & rotors to avoid warping, drastically increasing durability & service life over the competition
  • Engineered for Yamaha KT100 applications
  • Clutch driver comes included in package.

The TrailMaster Blazer 200 is an adult size kart and a Top Seller in our all new Blazer series. Loaded with all the most requested features, stunning new styling and exciting graphics, this model is a winner. Great looks, outstanding performance, extremely competitive pricing and world class support…it doesn’t get any better than that!

  • Stylish design
  • Exciting graphics
  • Five-point safety harness
  • Electric start with kill switch
  • Fully automatic with reverse, high performance 150cc GY6 engine with internal F-N-R
  • Adjustable steering wheel
  • Individual sports seats
  • Polished stainless steel muffler
  • LED headlight
  • Bikini sunshade top
  • Adjustable driver seat: pedal to seat back adjustable from 41” to 46”
  • Central rear view mirror
  • Rack and pinion steering wheel
  • Front and rear hydraulic disc brake
  • 4-point rear swing arm
  • Parking brake
  • 4-wheel stylish fenders
  • Trailer hitch
  • Large rear utility rack
  • Large gas tank

post_title: TrailMaster Cheetah 8 Youth & Adult Go Kart with Reverse
post_content:
Description

True to its namesake, the Cheetah is sleek, powerful, fast and agile with the power plant, drivetrain, suspension of a high performance go-kart and the functionality of a utility vehicle. Extra-long, independent front swing arms, a double ball joint, articulating rear suspension and ample ground clearance lets you glide over the roughest terrain and performing like independent suspension making it much harder to flip over. Adjustable high back bucket seats, and adjustable steering wheel will accommodate all shapes, sizes and skill level of the wild animal tamers in your family.

Automatic CVT with reverse, hydraulic disk brake, parking brake, fenders, canopy top and cargo rack are just a few of the many special features. Add the dramatic body panels and the LED light package with flowing turn signals and this is one cool cat!

The TrailMaster Cheetah 8 is a little bit smaller in size comparing to the Cheetah 150. It targets from youth to adult up to 5’8” while comparing the Cheetah 150/150X up to 6”2!

The Cheetah 8 equips with 208cc, 7.5 HP horizontal OHV Engine; Torque converter CVT transmission allows this beast takes off with ease. Its top speed can reach up to 32M/H. The manual choke allows this unit to start easy even under cold temperatures. A pull cord kill switch is another safety feature add to this unit.

We can ship it to you MOSTLY ASSEMBLED! with this option selected, only roll bars, head rests and battery will need to be installed. This cuts assembly time from about 2 hours down to about 20 minutes! And it is assembled by professionals! Not to mention no need for special tools such as forklift to lift up the unit to install the wheels. Assembled vehicles must still be uncrated and setup by customer’s qualified mechanic prior to operation.

  • Sporty stylish design
  • Articulating rear suspension equipped with anti-flip pull belts, much harder to roll over comparing to other rear solid axle machines
  • Youth/Adult size
  • Adjustable driver seat: pedal to seat back adjustable from 32” to 39”, fits person up to 5’8”
  • Pull cord kill switch

post_content:
Description

The Mini ROK engine is aimed at the younger generation of kart drivers, and is used for the Mini ROK class and Micro ROK class (with restrictions, see below).Thanks to some of its key features it is safe and easy to use, so that young drivers can become familiar with the kart without tension.

The engine has the following features: Single-cylinder 2 stroke engine, displacement 60cc, piston port. Air-cooled, equipped with centrifugal dry-clutch and integrated electrical starter.

The engine comes in two configurations, bare engine or in a complete kit with  Dell’Orto PHBG Ø 18mm carburettor, Dell’Orto fuel pump, Vortex intake silencer and exhaust with integrated exhaust silencer, starter complete with battery and battery support.

Mini Rok engine is aimed at the younger generation and for more than a decade has spread worldwide, therefore more and more federations have chosen it as national entry level category.

Micro ROK engine restrictions: spec gear (82); spec jet (95); restricted exhaust header. See the ROK Cup USA Rulebook for complete rules and regulations concerning engines for a particular class.

Specifications:

  • Single-cylinder 2 stroke engine
  • Displacement 60 cc
  • Piston Port
  • Air-cooled system
  • Integrated electrical starter
  • Centrifugal dry-clutch
  • Mixture-lubricated
  • Cast iron made cylinder CNC worked
  • 2 transfer ducts intake
  • Oval exhaust without rib
  • Piston ring L type
  • Radial bearing C4
  • Bore and stroke 42x43mm
  • 10 HP at 11.000 Rpm
  • Max torque 6.5 Nm at 9.000 Rpm
  • Max 15.500 Rpm
  • Selettra analogic ignition
  • Dell’Orto PHBG Ø 18mm carburettor
  • Vortex intake silencer
